      "content": "Schools are increasingly adopting these lessons because they are responding to a societal push for diversity and inclusion, framing it as a matter of modern educational best practices. Proponents argue that schools have a duty to prepare students for a diverse world and ensure every child feels safe and respected. Critics, however, see this as an overreach, believing that fundamental discussions about personal identity should remain solely within the private sphere of the family.",
