      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. it just feels like whenever i talk to my neighbors, the people who support it talk about it in terms of \"progress\" and \"science,\" and they make it sound like anyone who disagrees is just being closed-minded or hateful. but then the other side seems to get labeled as \"anti-science\" or \"extremist\" by the media. is there a way to look at it where both sides have actual, valid points, or is one side's argument fundamentally more grounded in reality?",
